      <title>CSS Grid Layout: Building Modern Web Layouts</title>
      <link>https://example.org/posts/css-grid-layout/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 17 Jun 2024 12:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://example.org/posts/css-grid-layout/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;CSS Grid is a powerful layout system that makes creating complex, responsive web layouts easier than ever. It&amp;rsquo;s a two-dimensional system that can handle both columns and rows, unlike Flexbox which is primarily one-dimensional.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;why-css-grid&#34;&gt;Why CSS Grid?&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Traditional layout methods like floats and positioning were never designed for the complex layouts we build today. CSS Grid was specifically created to solve layout problems, offering:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Two-dimensional control&lt;/strong&gt;: Manage both rows and columns simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsive by default&lt;/strong&gt;: Built-in features for responsive design&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Simplified markup&lt;/strong&gt;: Less need for wrapper divs and clearfix hacks&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alignment control&lt;/strong&gt;: Easy centering and alignment options&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;basic-grid-setup&#34;&gt;Basic Grid Setup&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-css&#34; data-lang=&#34;css&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;.&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;container&lt;/span&gt; {&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;display&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;grid&lt;/span&gt;;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;grid-template-columns&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;fr &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;fr &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;fr;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;grid-template-rows&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;auto&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;fr &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;auto&lt;/span&gt;;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;gap&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;20&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;px&lt;/span&gt;;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;height&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;vh&lt;/span&gt;;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;}&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;key-concepts&#34;&gt;Key Concepts&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grid Container&lt;/strong&gt;: The parent element with &lt;code&gt;display: grid&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
